[V1]
.F                  C     F
 Take my life, and let it be 
.F   Dm  Bb  Gm   F/C   C7  F
 con-se-cra-ted, Lord, to thee. ||
.F         C       C7     F
 Take my moments and my days; 
.F         Bb   F  C    F       C
 let them flow in ceaseless praise ||
.Dm    C    F   Bb   F   C     F
 let them flow in ceaseless praise 
 
 
[V2]
.F                   C        F
 Take my hands, and let them move 
.F   Dm  Bb  Gm  F/C  C7  F
 at the im-pulse of thy love. ||
.F        C        C7        F
 Take my feet, and let them be 
.F          Bb  F  C    F    C
 swift and beau-ti-ful for thee ||
.Dm     C   F  Bb  F    C     F
 swift and beau-ti-ful for thee 
 
 
[V3]
.F                   C      F
 Take my voice, and let me sing 
.F   Dm  Bb  Gm  F/C  C7  F
 always, on-ly, for my King. ||
.F        C        C7        F
 Take my lips, and let them be 
.F           Bb  F  C    F    C
 filled with mes-sa-ges from thee ||
.Dm       C   F  Bb  F   C     F
 filled with mes-sa-ges from thee 
 
 
[V4]
.F               C      F
 Take my silver and my gold; 
.F   Dm  Bb  Gm   F/C  C7  F
 not a mite would I with-hold. ||
.F        C     C7       F
 Take my intellect, and use 
.F      Bb    F   C    F     C
 every power as thou shalt choose ||
.Dm  C  F     Bb   F   C    F
 every power as thou shalt choose
 
 
[V5]
.F                  C       F
 Take my will, and make it thine; 
.F   Dm  Bb  Gm  F/C  C7  F
 it shall be no long-er mine. ||
.F         C        C7       F
 Take my heart, it is thine own; 
.F        Bb  F   C   F  C
 it shall be thy ro-yal throne ||
.Dm  C    F  Bb   F   C    F
 it shall be thy ro-yal throne 
 
 
[V6]
.F                 C       F
 Take my love, my Lord, I pour 
.F   Dm  Bb   Gm   F/C  C7    F
 at thy feet its treasure store. ||
.F        C        C7     F
 Take my self, and I will be 
.F      Bb  F   C    F  C
 ever, on-ly, all for thee. ||
.Dm  C  F  Bb   F   C    F
 ever, on-ly, all for thee.
 
 
